# Node Cloud Polling Api Runtime

Generated PiPhi integration runtime.

## Run locally

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
npm run build
npm run test
npm run validate
```

The runtime listens on port `9988` by default and exposes the common PiPhi runtime route contract:

- `GET /health`
- `GET /diagnostics`
- `POST /discover`
- `POST /config`
- `POST /config/sync`
- `POST /deconfigure`
- `POST /deconfigure/{config_id}`
- `GET /state`
- `GET /contract`
- `GET /entities`
- `GET /events`
- `POST /events/device/{config_id}/example`
- `POST /telemetry/example`
- `POST /telemetry/device/{config_id}/example`
- `POST /command`

## Manifest

`manifest.json` is a starter manifest. Before publishing, update:

- `image`
- `version`
- capabilities and commands
- config fields and identity fields
- entity metadata

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t piphinetwork/node-cloud-polling-api-runtime:0.1.0 .
docker run --rm -p 9988:9988 piphinetwork/node-cloud-polling-api-runtime:0.1.0
```
